abstract: Google’s better-than-expected performance in the third quarter included $2.17 billion in net income on $7.29 billion in revenue.

lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Google has spent the last few months arguing to anyone who will listen that its new advertising businesses  including ads with images and video and on cellphones  will fuel its next phase of growth. On Thursday, the company finally gave some numbers to support the claim.

headline.print_headline: Google Finds Income In Other Than Search
